                "title": "Garden Use",
                "type": "String",
                "value": "Black nightshade is often grown in gardens as an accent or specimen plant. Gardeners value its attractive star-shaped flowers in the summer and green then black berries in the autumn. Black nightshade is suitable for trellises and alongside walls in pollinator gardens. It may comfortably grow in a coastal setting.",
